The paper deals with algorithms for analyzing transition systems, which are commonly used in formal verification and model checking. This topic falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions Kripke structures, labeled graphs, labeled transition systems, and automata, which are all related to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). The notion of stability of a preorder with respect to a coarser one is also related to formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the paper proposes efficient algorithms for simulation, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
